    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Configure and Use Octopress on Ubuntu]]></title>
    <link href="http://en.jiapeng.me/2013/10/13/configure-and-use-octopress-on-ubuntu/"/>
    <updated>2013-10-13T11:04:00+08:00</updated>
    <id>http://en.jiapeng.me/2013/10/13/configure-and-use-octopress-on-ubuntu</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><em>Set Up a Octopress Environment and Use It!</em></p>

<!-- more -->


<h2>Set Up Enviroment</h2>

<h3>Ruby</h3>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ sudo su
</span><span class='line'># curl -L https://get.rvm.io | bash -s stable --ruby
</span><span class='line'># rvm install 1.9.3
</span><span class='line'># rvm --default use 1.9.3
</span><span class='line'># rvm rubygems lates</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>For me, i need enable <code>rvm</code> by checking <strong>Edit &ndash;> Profile Preferences &ndash;> Title and Command &ndash;> Command &ndash;> Run command as log in shell</strong> in gnome terminal.<br/>
<a href="https://rvm.io/integration/gnome-terminal">Detailed Explation</a></p>

<h3>Configure Octopress</h3>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ git clone git://github.com/imathis/octopress.git octopress
</span><span class='line'>$ cd octopress
</span><span class='line'>$ sudo gem install bundler
</span><span class='line'>$ sudo bundle install</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h3>Proxy</h3>

<p><code>gem</code> source is fucked by GFW sometimes, run these to command to use a proxy:</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>// need a proxy(GoAgent, Wallproxy ect) first, and replace the ip below
</span><span class='line'>$ http_proxy="http://127.0.0.1:8087"
</span><span class='line'>$ export http_proxy</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h2>Blog basic</h2>

<p>Here are some commands which are used most frequently.</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>// Create new post
</span><span class='line'>$ bundle exec rake new_post["name"]
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>// preview
</span><span class='line'>$ bundle exec rake preview
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>// publish
</span><span class='line'>$ bundle exec rake generate
</span><span class='line'>$ bundle exec rake deploy</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>

]]></content>
